      "acceptanceCriteria": "The QoI (relative hemolysis index RH) is directly linked to the clinical decision criterion and is sensitive to the dimensional variations under study.",
      "rationale": "RH is the FDA-recognized metric for comparative hemolysis assessment. Sensitivity analysis confirmed that impeller clearance and blade angle variations produce measurable RH changes (>5% per 0.1 mm clearance change), confirming relevance. Gradation 2 met."
